The paper discusses an information theoretic interpretation of deep learning, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the dynamics of the machinery of deep neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning in computer vision, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
